Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with oil and half of the @smoked paprika{1}.

Then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}.

On a baking tray, combine the pepper and tomatoes. Add a drizzle of oil and half of the @harissa paste{50}. Season with salt and pepper and use your hands to coat the veggies in the paste and oil. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and soft, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Pop half the red onion in a #small bowl{} and add the @cider vinegar{15} and the @sugar{1}. Add a pinch of salt, mix together and set aside.

Heat a splash of oil in a large #frying pan{} over a medium high heat. When hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{260} and cook, stirring occasionally until golden brown all over, ~{7-10%minutes}.

Once the chicken is golden, add the remaining smoked paprika and @honey{15}, cook until the chicken is fully coated and shiny, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with salt.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle, wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Crumble the @feta cheese{100} into a small bowl. Add half to the sweet potato wedges and bake until it begins to brown ~{5-10%minutes}.

In a small bowl combine the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75} with the remaining harissa paste. Drain your pickled onions.

Pop the @Greek style flatbreads{4} in the oven until warm and starting to turn golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Alternatively pop them in your #toaster{} if it's easier.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all).

Pop the flatbreads on your plates. Spread half of the harissa yogurt evenly over the flat breads. Top with the roasted vegetables followed by the glazed chicken.

Sprinkle the pickled red onions and remaining feta over the chicken followed by the coriander. Drizzle over the remaining yogurt. Serve the sweet potato wedges on the side. Enjoy!